cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for improving deep learning performance with small labeled training sets by applying data augmentation to unlabeled data in a semi-supervised learning setting. The method is evaluated on language and vision tasks, indicating relevance to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of state-of-the-art data augmentation methods and consistency training also suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
